Forking paths - second study

1 Introduction

This notebook generates the results of the second study in the paper Forking paths in empirical studies available on SSRN.
The dataset for this part comes from Dacheng Xius website (https://dachxiu.chicagobooth.edu/) and was slightly altered. It is a bit heavy and can be downloaded here.

WARNING: he code for this part takes much longer, roughly 11 hours on a 2018 MacBook Pro.

First, we load packages & import the data.
Below, we work with 6 characteristics, so the results will differ from those of the paper.

3 The modules

Empirical work in the paper is modelled as chains of modules.

module_variable <- function(data, variable){
    #save(variable, file = paste0(Sys.time(), "_variable.RData"))
    if(!(variable %in% c("mvel1", "retvol"))){
        return(data %>% 
                   dplyr::select(all_of(c("permno", "Date", "Return", "mvel1", "retvol", variable))) %>%
                   purrr::set_names(c("permno", "Date", "Return", "mvel1", "retvol", "variable")))
    }
    if(variable == "mvel1"){
        return(data %>% 
                   dplyr::select(all_of(c("permno", "Date", "Return", "mvel1", "retvol"))) %>%
                   mutate(variable = mvel1))
    }
    if(variable == "retvol"){
        return(data %>% 
                   dplyr::select(all_of(c("permno", "Date", "Return", "mvel1", "retvol"))) %>%
                   mutate(variable = retvol))
    }    
}

impute <- function(v){
    v[is.na(v)] <- median(v, na.rm = T)
    return(v)
}

module_imputation <- function(data, imputation){
    if(imputation == 0){return(data)}
    if(imputation == 1){
        return(
            data %>% 
                group_by(Date) %>%
                mutate(variable = impute(variable)) %>%
                ungroup()
        )
    }
}

module_horizon <- function(data, horizon){
    vol_thresh <- 0.001 # hard-coded!
    if(horizon == 1){return(data %>% na.omit() %>% filter(retvol > vol_thresh))}
    if(horizon == 2){
        return(data %>%
                   group_by(permno) %>%
                   mutate(Return = (Return + dplyr::lead(Return)) / horizon) %>% # Returns are scaled to the monthly scale
                   ungroup() %>%
                   na.omit() %>% filter(retvol > vol_thresh))
    }
    if(horizon == 3){
        return(data %>%
                   group_by(permno) %>%
                   mutate(Return = (Return + dplyr::lead(Return) + dplyr::lead(Return, 2)) / horizon) %>%
                   ungroup() %>%
                   na.omit() %>% filter(retvol > vol_thresh))
    }
}

module_start <- function(data, start_quantile){
    L <- nrow(data)
    data[ceiling(L*start_quantile):L, ]
}

module_stop <- function(data, stop_quantile){
    L <- nrow(data)
    data[1:ceiling(L*stop_quantile), ]
}

module_thresh_type <- function(data, thresh_type){
    type <- substr(thresh_type,(nchar(thresh_type)-1),nchar(thresh_type))
    thresh <- substr(thresh_type, 1, (nchar(thresh_type)-3)) %>% as.numeric()
    if(type == "EW"){
        return(list(t = data %>%
                        group_by(Date) %>%
                        mutate(type = case_when(
                            variable <= quantile(variable, thresh, na.rm = T) ~ "Short",
                            variable >= quantile(variable, 1 - thresh, na.rm = T) ~ "Long")
                        ) %>%
                        # mutate(type = if_else(variable < quantile(variable, thresh, na.rm = T), "Short",
                        #                       if_else(variable > quantile(variable, 1 - thresh, na.rm = T), "Long", "Neutral"))) %>%
                        pivot_wider(names_from = "type", values_from = "Return") %>%
                        group_by(Date) %>%
                        summarize(ret = mean(Long, na.rm = T) - mean(Short, na.rm = T)) %>%
                        summarise(m = mean(ret, na.rm = T),
                                  s = sd(ret, na.rm = T),
                                  n = length(ret)) %>% as.numeric()))    # Returns monthly avg returns & vol 
    }
    if(type == "VW"){
        return(list(t = data %>%
                        group_by(Date) %>%
                        mutate(type = case_when(
                            variable <= quantile(variable, thresh, na.rm = T) ~ "Short",
                            variable >= quantile(variable, 1 - thresh, na.rm = T) ~ "Long")
                        ) %>%                       
                        # mutate(type = if_else(variable < quantile(variable, thresh, na.rm = T), "Short",
                        #                       if_else(variable > quantile(variable, 1 - thresh, na.rm = T), "Long", "Neutral"))) %>%
                        pivot_wider(names_from = "type", values_from = "Return") %>%
                        mutate(is_Long = is.finite(Long),
                               is_Short = is.finite(Short)) %>%
                        group_by(Date) %>%
                        summarize(ret = sum(Long*mvel1, na.rm = T)/sum(is_Long*mvel1, na.rm = T) - 
                                      sum(Short*mvel1, na.rm = T)/sum(is_Short*mvel1, na.rm = T)) %>%
                        summarise(m = mean(ret, na.rm = T),
                                  s = sd(ret, na.rm = T),
                                  n = length(ret)) %>% as.numeric()))    # Returns monthly avg returns & vol 
    }
    if(type == "IW"){
        return(list(t = data %>%
                        group_by(Date) %>%
                        mutate(type = case_when(
                            variable <= quantile(variable, thresh, na.rm = T) ~ "Short",
                            variable >= quantile(variable, 1 - thresh, na.rm = T) ~ "Long")
                        ) %>%                       
                        # mutate(type = if_else(variable < quantile(variable, thresh, na.rm = T), "Short",
                        #                       if_else(variable > quantile(variable, 1 - thresh, na.rm = T), "Long", "Neutral"))) %>%
                        pivot_wider(names_from = "type", values_from = "Return") %>%
                        mutate(is_Long = is.finite(Long),
                               is_Short = is.finite(Short)) %>%
                        group_by(Date) %>%
                        summarize(ret = sum(Long/retvol, na.rm = T)/sum(is_Long/retvol, na.rm = T) - 
                                      sum(Short/retvol, na.rm = T)/sum(is_Short/retvol, na.rm = T)) %>%
                        summarise(m = mean(ret, na.rm = T),
                                  s = sd(ret, na.rm = T),
                                  n = length(ret)) %>% as.numeric()))    # Returns monthly avg returns & vol 
    }    
}

The aggregation.

module_aggregator <- function(variable = variable,
                              imputation = imputation,
                              horizon = horizon,
                              start_quantile = start_quantile,
                              stop_quantile = stop_quantile,
                              thresh_type = thresh_type){
    data_paths %>%
        module_variable(variable = variable) %>%
        module_imputation(imputation = imputation) %>%
        module_horizon(horizon = horizon) %>%
        module_start(start_quantile = start_quantile) %>%
        module_stop(stop_quantile = stop_quantile) %>%
        module_thresh_type(thresh_type = thresh_type)
}

# Test!

                  imputation = 0,
                  horizon = 1,
                  start_quantile = 0,
                  stop_quantile = 1/3,
                  thresh_type = "0.1_EW")

Surprisingly, we discovered that slicing the parallelization improves its speed, hence the slightly heavy loop below.
Running the future_map() function over 44K parameters was too slow (and penalizing upon errors).

4 The main run

Below, we specify the layer options and launch the spanning of all paths. For each anomaly, one output file is created with the *_results_fork.RData* suffix.

imputation <- c(0,1)
horizon <- 1:3
start_quantile <- c(0, 1/3, 2/3)
stop_quantile <- c(1/3, 2/3, 1)
thresh <- c(0.1, 0.15, 0.2, 0.25, 0.3)
type <- c("EW", "VW", "IW")
for(i in 1:length(features)){ # PB 63
    if(i%%5==0){print(i)}
    variable <- features[i]
    pars <- expand_grid(variable, imputation, horizon, start_quantile, stop_quantile, thresh, type) %>%
        filter(stop_quantile > start_quantile)
    pars2 <- pars %>% mutate(thresh_type = paste0(thresh, "_", type)) %>%
        select(-thresh, -type)
    plan(multisession, workers = 4)                                # Set the number of cores
    if(i%%10==0){tictoc::tic()}                                    # Launch timer
    output <- future_pmap_dfr(pars2,  module_aggregator)           # Parallel routine
    if(i%%10==0){tictoc::toc()}                                    # Stop timer
    results <- cbind(pars, matrix(output$t, ncol = 3, byrow = T))  # Bind parameters to results
    colnames(results)[8:10] <- c("avg_return", "vol", "n")
    save(results, file = paste0(variable, "_results_fork.RData"))    
}

Then, all the output files must be transferred in a separate folder within the main folder. Below, we call it output.

results_full <- c()

6 Boostrap

First, we need baseline results for the anomalies.
We consider 2 month holding periods, over the whole sample, with a breakpoint at 0.2 (i.e.0.8 for the upper tail).

module_fixed <- function(data){ # This is the final module with fixed values, weighting is EW
    thresh <- 0.2
    data %>%
        group_by(Date) %>%
        mutate(type = case_when(
            variable <= quantile(variable, thresh, na.rm = T) ~ "Short",
            variable >= quantile(variable, 1 - thresh, na.rm = T) ~ "Long")
        ) %>%
        # mutate(type = if_else(variable < quantile(variable, thresh, na.rm = T), "Short",
        #                       if_else(variable > quantile(variable, 1 - thresh, na.rm = T), "Long", "Neutral"))) %>%
        pivot_wider(names_from = "type", values_from = "Return") %>%
        group_by(Date) %>%
        summarize(ret = mean(Long, na.rm = T) - mean(Short, na.rm = T))   # Returns monthly  returns 
}


mod_horz <- 2
m_testing <- matrix(0, ncol = length(features), nrow = length(dates)-mod_horz)
for(v in 1:length(features)){
    if(v %% 20 == 0 ){print(v)}
    m_testing[,v] <- data_paths %>% 
        module_variable(features[v]) %>%
        module_imputation(1) %>%
        module_horizon(mod_horz) %>%
        module_start(0) %>%
        module_stop(1) %>%
        module_fixed() %>%
        pull(ret)
}

Next we can turn to multiple testing.
We implement the bootstrap reality check (BRC) of White (2020) (https://www.jstor.org/stable/2999444), as described in Harvey et al.(2020) (https://academic.oup.com/raps/article/10/2/199/5817321).
We use blocks of size 12 (annual series of 12 consecutive months).

block_boot <- function(X, block_size = 12){            # This function is for simple bootstrap
    TT <- nrow(X)
    l <- floor(TT/block_size)
    ind <- sample(1:(TT-block_size+1), l, replace = F) # No index twice
    Z <- c()
    for(j in 1:l){
        Z <- rbind(Z, X[ind[j]:(ind[j]+block_size-1),])
    }
    remainz <- TT - floor(TT/block_size) * block_size
    Z <- rbind(Z, X[sample(1:TT, remainz),])
    return(Z)
}

brc <- function(X, block_size = 12, B = 10){           # This codes the BRC
    Z <- array(0, dim = c(B, nrow(X), ncol(X)))
    mu <- apply(X, 2, mean)
    mu <- matrix(mu, nrow = B, ncol = ncol(X), byrow = T)
    for(b in 1:B){
        Z[b,,] <- block_boot(X, block_size)
    }
    mu_B <- apply(Z, c(1,3), mean) - mu
    s_B <- apply(Z, c(1,3), sd)
    mu_B/s_B*sqrt(nrow(X)) 
}

# Below we make sure anomalies are in the correct direction
for(j in 1:ncol(m_testing)){
    if(sum(m_testing[,j]) < 0){m_testing[,j] = -m_testing[,j]}
}


t_testing <- brc(m_testing, 12, 540) %>% t()
t_testing <- apply(t_testing, 2, sort)

7 Exhaustive Multiple Testing

We can then combine paths-generated outputs and multiple testing and compare to bootstrapped series.

library(tidyverse)
load("results_full.RData")
m <- results_full %>%
    mutate(m = avg_return) %>%
    filter(imputation == 1,
           horizon == 2,
           start_quantile == 0,
           stop_quantile == 1,
           thresh == 0.2,
           type == "EW") %>%
    select(all_of(c("variable", "m")))
m_max <- results_full %>%
    filter(imputation == 1,
           horizon == 2,
           start_quantile == 0,
           stop_quantile == 1,
           thresh == 0.2,
           type == "EW") %>%
    mutate(t = abs(sqrt(n) * avg_return/vol)) %>%
    pull(t) %>%
    max()
t_exhaust_1 <- results_full %>%
    left_join(m, by = "variable") %>%
    mutate(t = sqrt(n)*(avg_return-m)/vol,
           id = row_number()) %>%
    group_by(variable) %>%
    mutate(m_t = mean(t),
           t = t*sign(m_t)) %>% # Correct direction
    ungroup() %>% 
    select(all_of(c("variable", "t"))) %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = variable, values_from = t) %>%
    tidyr::unnest() %>%
    as.matrix() %>%
    t()
t_exhaust_2 <- results_full %>%
    left_join(m, by = "variable") %>%
    mutate(t = sqrt(n)*(avg_return-mean(avg_return))/vol,
           id = row_number()) %>%
    group_by(variable) %>%
    mutate(m_t = mean(t),
           t = t*sign(m_t)) %>% # Correct direction
    ungroup() %>% 
    select(all_of(c("variable", "t"))) %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = variable, values_from = t) %>%
    tidyr::unnest() %>%
    as.matrix() %>%
    t()
t_exhaust_1 <- apply(t_exhaust_1, 2, sort)
t_exhaust_2 <- apply(t_exhaust_2, 2, sort)
